Days of the month are a special counter and often have altered readings. It can take some memorization to get used to this.

The first day of the month is an exception [1日]{ついたち}.
Days 2-10 use the 訓読み reading plus か.
Day 14 and 24 use a hybrid reading [十四日]{じゅう・よっか}.
Day 20 is another exception [二十日]{はつか}.
The rest of the days use the 音読み reading plus にち.
